To ensure that all Wikipedia content is [[Wikipedia:Verifiability|verifiable]], anyone may question an [[Wikipedia:Citing sources#When and why to cite sources|un-cited claim]] by inserting a <code>{{tl|Citation needed}}</code> tag.

{{quotation|'''Example:''' 65% of people believe in ghosts.<!--{{Citation needed}} begin-->{{fix |link=Wikipedia:Citation needed#Citation needed |text=citation needed |class=noprint Template-Fact }}<!--{{Citation needed}} end--> }}

* Exercise caution before relying upon unsourced claims.
* If you can provide a [[Wikipedia:Identifying reliable sources|reliable source]] for the claim, please [[Wikipedia:Be bold|be bold]] and [[Wikipedia:Tutorial/Editing|replace]] the "Citation needed" template with enough information to locate the source.  You may leave the [[Copy editing|copyediting]] to someone else, or learn more about [[Wikipedia:Citing sources|citing sources on Wikipedia]].
* If someone tagged your contributions with "Citation needed" and you disagree, discuss the matter on the article's [[Help:Using talk pages|discussion page]].
* Controversial, poorly-sourced claims in biographies of living people [[Wikipedia:Biographies of living persons#Remove unsourced or poorly sourced contentious material|should be deleted immediately]].

